(numRXQEntries, nDCacheWays): C: Network receive queue entries and data cache associativity are independent hardware design choices with no causal relationship;
(numRXQEntries, numRCQEntries): C: While both are network interface queue parameters, RXQ and RCQ serve different functions and their sizes are typically independent design decisions;
(numRXQEntries, flush): C: Network receive queue configuration does not directly cause CPU pipeline flushes as they operate in different system domains;
